        <bioghist id="ref2">
            <head>Historical/Biographical Note</head>
            <p>John L. Simon was a psychiatrist who served in the Spanish Civil War as a medic and later became an active member of the Veterans of the Abraham Lincoln Brigade.</p>
        </bioghist>
        <scopecontent id="ref1">
            <head>Scope and Contents note</head>
            <p>This small collection contains copies of FBI files on John L. Simon obtained via a Freedom of Information Act request. The files concern Simon's life after World War II, covering the period circa 1949 to 1966.</p>
